Indeed, running out of swap gets you:

  Swap: 8192M Total, 8192M Used, K Free, 100% Inuse

Looking at display.c:summary_format(), if the value were zero it would just skip that field, but if it becomes negative it displays the field name without a value:

  if (num > 0)
    ..	
  /* ignore negative numbers, but display corresponding string */
  else if (num < 0)
  {
      p = stpcpy(p, thisname);
  }

Seems a bit arbitrary.
